## Verification Plan

### Per-Phase Testing
Each phase has its own verification checklist (detailed above). Run after completing each phase before moving to the next.

### Integration Testing
After Phase 5, run an end-to-end test:
1. Create a collection with 3 requests
2. Add assertions to each request (Phase 1)
3. Configure variable chaining (Phase 2)
4. Run the collection → verify all assertions pass and variables chain
5. Pin baselines (Phase 5) → re-run → verify no regression

### Full Suite Validation (after Phase 9)
1. Run the app with `expo start --android` / `--ios`
2. Execute each testing type and verify results display correctly
3. Verify Supabase data persistence (check tables for correct data)
4. Test cancellation/abort flows for all long-running operations
5. Verify navigation between all screens works correctly

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Development approach**: Build each phase as a complete, testable iteration. Don't start Phase N+1 until Phase N is verified. This matches the dependency chain — Phase 2 literally can't work without Phase 1's assertion engine.
